CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1958, pg. B7, reads: "PROUD - Reginald Wendell Bennett, left, received his Master of Science in bacteriology; and left to right, Lillie M. Lesesne, was awarded a Master in Letters in nursing education: Pauline Holland Hord, became the holder of a Bachelor of Science in nursing; and Charles Johnson Jr., of Atlanta, Ga., won his Master in Letters Degree in biology at the University of Pittsburgh"
TitMainTitle: University of Pittsburgh graduates Reginald Wendell Bennett with Master of Science in Bacteriology, Lillie M. Lesesne with Master in Letters in Nursing, Pauline Holland Hord with Bachelor of Science in Nursing, and Charles Johnson Jr. with Master in Letters in Biology, wearing dark caps and gowns, posed in front of Cathedral of Learning, Oakland
